The paper deals with privacy-preserving techniques for managing access to time-series data generated by sensors on mobile, IoT, and wearable devices. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Among these categories, cs.CR is the most likely category as the paper focuses on privacy-preserving techniques. The paper also proposes a novel feature-learning algorithm, which suggests that it could belong to the category of cs.LG. The paper's focus on wearable devices and health monitoring suggests that it could belong to the category of cs.CY. The paper's evaluation of the algorithm with an activity recognition task suggests that it could belong to the category of cs.SI. Finally, the paper's focus on protecting individuals' privacy suggests that it could belong to the category of cs.HC.
